  "decision": "The direction-dependent curvature branch is now characterized at the minimal block-isotypic level. Residual su(2)\u002Bu(1)-invariant block projectors exist and stabilized Landau-style block weights can select the doublet in target-blind algebraic menus, so the branch is not mathematically empty. However, pure direction-dependent quadratic curvature terms still run away on the Phase405/410 rank-1 flat rays, and every finite-VEV selector in the stabilized menu imports an extra block mass law plus an extra quartic stabilizer. The current GU sources define neither the direction-dependent curvature kernel nor its sign, scale, stabilizer, VEV amplitude, observed-field rows, weak-angle lineage, pole extraction, or GeV normalization. This phase therefore materializes the exact source-law shape needed for progress, but fills no Phase201 or Phase256 field and promotes no W/Z/H mass."
